SUMMARY:Three Colours
DESCRIPTION:Three of the six Hindustani gharanas\, each with its own repertoire of raags\, compositions and improvisation techniques. \nThis evening Mukul Kulkarni moves through each tradition\, with special attention to the three branches of the Gwalior gharana. Before every item\, he names the stylistic sources of what he is presenting\, illuminating the differences between traditions. He is accompanied by Sagar Bharatraj on tabla and Niranjan ‘Bharat’ Hegde on harmonium. A performance built around a well-trained artiste\, deep in a raag\, going somewhere no one\, not even the singer himself\, can predict. \nOne unhurried evening. Immersion and imagination.  \nSupported by:\n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/three-colours/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Music,Performing Arts
